        <h4 class="panel-title"><a href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/events-calendar?Page_ID=3610&id=773190" target="_blank">Paris 27th-29th March 2019 </a></h4>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h4><strong><strong>Hands on Sensory Statistics</strong></strong></h4>
        <p> A hands-on introduction to the statistical methods needed by  a sensory scientist. Learn how to analyse and interpret real life data  using  SENPAQ (included in course price)  and XLSTAT. Be guided through exercises with written solutions to take away  with you, so you can start analysing data with more confidence straight after  the course.<br>
        </p>
        <p>Taught by Anne Hasted</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/events-calendar?Page_ID=3610&id=773190" target="_blank">More Info</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-primary">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title"><a href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/events-calendar?Page_ID=3610&id=773220" target="_blank">Chicago 10th-12th April 2019</a></h4>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h4><strong>Hands on Consumer Driven Product Optimization</strong></h4>
        <p>Designed to give  you the knowledge, practice and tools to analyse and interpret consumer test  data and to optimise the sensory properties of food, beverages and personal  care products.  Gain confidence in  analysis of your data using XLSTAT, which method to use when and which outputs  to present, using our exercises with written solutions and interpretations.</p>
        <p>Taught by Anne Hasted</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/events-calendar?Page_ID=3610&id=773220" target="_blank">More Info</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
