<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="panel panel-primary">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title"><a href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/upcoming-training/qi-hal-macfie-courses?id=773247" target="_blank">Windsor 15th May 2019</a></h4>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h4><strong><strong>Analysis of Variance Masterclass</strong></strong></h4>
        <p>This one-day  workshop gives you the opportunity to consider issues that we are sure you  worry about from time to time in your everyday analysis of consumer and sensory  test data. Our key tool is Analysis of Variance but this technique makes  assumptions about the underlying distributions in our data – what are these  assumptions and do they matter?We will also cover mixed models, repeated  measures analysis, when and how it should be used and look at simple nested  models.</p>
        <p>Taught by Anne Hasted</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/upcoming-training/qi-hal-macfie-courses?id=773247" target="_blank">More Info</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-primary">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title"><a href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/upcoming-training/qi-hal-macfie-courses" target="_blank">Windsor 17th May 2019</a></h4>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h4><strong>Introduction to Bayesian Methods for Sensory & Consumer Data</strong><br>
        </h4>
        <p> Bayesian statistical analysis has been successfully  used in other industries for many years now, yet is rarely seen in the Sensory  and Consumer world. In this one-day course, we give you the  understanding to the key concepts of these analysis methods, that need to be  understood before a Bayesian study can be set-up. We give information on how to  interpret and apply results of a Bayesian analysis to improve decision making  ability and so maximising use of your data.</p>
        <p>Taught by Gemma Hodgson and Mary Jenner</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/upcoming-training/qi-hal-macfie-courses" target="_blank">More Info</a></p>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="panel panel-primary">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title"><a href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/upcoming-training/qi-hal-macfie-courses" target="_blank">Windsor 17th May 2019</a></h4>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h4><strong>How Significant is Significance?</strong><br>
        </h4>
        <p>A half day session highlighting the problems we all  have in communicating statistical test results  to our audience. We will refresh your minds about the correct interpretation of significance,  discuss the over reliance on p-values, encourage wider use of confidence  intervals, Consider other alternatives and finish the morning with the thorny  topic of multiple comparison tests.<br>
        </p>
        <p>Led by Anne Hasted</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/upcoming-training/qi-hal-macfie-courses" target="_blank">More Info</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-primary">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title"><a href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/upcoming-training/qi-hal-macfie-courses" target="_blank">Singapore 28th-30th May 2019</a></h4>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h4><strong>Hands on Sensory Statistics</strong></h4>
        <p>A hands-on introduction to the statistical methods needed by  a sensory scientist. Learn how to analyse and interpret real life data  using  SENPAQ (included in course price)  and XLSTAT. Be guided through exercises with written solutions to take away  with you, so you can start analysing data with more confidence straight after  the course.<br>
        </p>
        <p>Taught by Thierry Worch</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="https://www.qistatistics.co.uk/upcoming-training/qi-hal-macfie-courses" target="_blank">More Info</a><br>
